Except as provided in subparagraph (iv) of this paragraph, the Governor shall appoint 1 professional member from a list of qualified individuals submitted to the Governor by each of the following organizations:
The Monumental City Medical Society;
The Medical and Chirurgical Faculty of the State of Maryland;
The faculty of the University of Maryland School of Medicine; and
The faculties of the Johns Hopkins Medical Institutions.

The terms of the voting members are staggered as required by the terms provided for voting members of the Advisory Council on July 1, 1982. The terms of those members end as follows:
3 in 1983;
3 in 1984;
3 in 1985; and
2 in 1986.
